def anonymize_data(data, columns):
    for column in columns:
        data[column] = data[column].apply(lambda x: hashlib.sha256(str(x).encode()).hexdigest())
    return data

tiktok_users_anonymized = anonymize_data(tiktok_users, ['account_id', 'nickname', 'bio_link', 'profile_pic_url', 'url'])

features = tiktok_users_anonymized[['followers', 'following', 'likes', 'videos_count']].fillna(0)
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=5, random_state=0).fit(features)
tiktok_users_anonymized['segment'] = kmeans.labels_
In [12]:
def recommend_content(user_id, content_data):
    # Filter out the current user from the data
    user_data = content_data[content_data['account_id'] == user_id]
    other_data = content_data[content_data['account_id'] != user_id]
    
    # Only use numerical columns for similarity calculation
    numerical_columns = ['followers', 'following', 'likes', 'videos_count', 'segment']
    user_interactions = user_data[numerical_columns].to_numpy()
    other_data_matrix = other_data[numerical_columns].to_numpy()
    
    # Calculate cosine similarity
    similarity_scores = cosine_similarity(user_interactions, other_data_matrix).flatten()
    
    # Get top 5 recommendations
    recommendations_indices = similarity_scores.argsort()[::-1][:5]
    recommendations = other_data.iloc[recommendations_indices]
    
    return recommendations

def analyze_user_behaviour(data):
    # Perform statistical analysis to find patterns and trends in user behaviour
    correlation_matrix = data.corr()
    print(correlation_matrix)

    # Visualize the data
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    plt.matshow(correlation_matrix, fignum=1)
    plt.xticks(range(len(correlation_matrix.columns)), correlation_matrix.columns, rotation=90)
    plt.yticks(range(len(correlation_matrix.columns)), correlation_matrix.columns)
    plt.colorbar()
    plt.title('Correlation Matrix')
    plt.show()
